<br>
I have a mage who is in command of a mercenary company, and I like to sit in my tent, and conjure a globe shaped scrying point over the battle field and have the view surround me, and I stand in the center.  It's like my own little Membari holographic command room thingy to lead the battle with.  It really wows the subordinates too.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukehvrynne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kehvrynne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/19/02 6:38:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: spells, got to love them.</span><hr size=1> I prefer &quot;thinking rogue's&quot; spells like <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Item</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rope Trick</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Audible Glamour</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Change Self</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Sleep</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Much more elegant than messy stuff like <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magic Missile</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Fireball</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  I once overcame a chance encounter with a minotaur with judicious use of Audible Glamour.  The entire party was at best Level 3, and were foolish enough to close for melee.  <br>
<br>
 <p>Kehvrynne Quickblade, Professional Damsel of Distress<br>
